author: Matthew Fairburn | mfairburn@syracuse.com
title: Tyrod Taylor missing from Buffalo Bills' Thursday practice in London
text:
Hertfordshire, England â€” The Buffalo Bills were without starting quarterback Tyrod Taylor for the start of their Thursday practice in London.
Taylor, who missed the Bills' Week 6 loss to the Cincinnati Bengals with a sprained MCL suffered the week earlier, practiced Wednesday and split reps with EJ Manuel. Taylor said he was able to do significantly more than he was able to do the week before, but his absence from Thursday practice is not a positive sign for his availability when the Bills play against the Jaguars in London.
Meanwhile, wide receiver Sammy Watkins was at practice but did not participate.
